description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse, a newly qualified Nurse, or training to be a Nurse? Are you looking for an exciting and interesting role, working with a multi-disciplinary team who are committed to delivering high quality and safe patient care? If you are motivated, dedicated, passionate and looking for a new challenge to enhance your personal and professional development, then we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 27 bedded, mixed Trauma Ward, specialising in hip fractures of our older patients giving a mixture of Surgery and Medicine. Our patients, admitted through A&amp;E, are frail and vulnerable and require the care of professionals who are dedicated and understanding of their complex needs. This is an ideal opportunity for someone who has a passion for providing high quality patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside a unique team of Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists and Ortho-Geriatric Consultants, we also provide rehabilitation and support to enable the patients to leave the hospital environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong team, with great opportunities to develop and gain excellent experience in delivering compassionate and safe care to this complex and vulnerable group of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities to work alongside Fracture Clinic and Theatres make this an ideal opportunity for a nurse who is passionate at seeing their patients effectively through the patient pathway. With our links to Canterbury Christ Church University and in-house nurse development team, we are also dedicated to providing education and training to support you in your CPD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love to meet you and show you around. For more information or to arrange a site visit, please contact Carol Allen, Ward Manager, on 01233 616795 or by email carolallen2@nhs.net or Angela Pearson - angela.pearson1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
